The paper focuses on analyzing ad exchanges from a game-theoretic perspective, specifically using combinatorial auctions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the trading of advertisement slots on the web, which falls under the domain of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of ad networks as mediators also suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also discusses the incentives of all three involved parties, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with competitive equilibrium, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.EC (Economics and Computation) sub-category.
